1
00:00:11,267 --> 00:00:20,833
This is how we talk to AI today - one message after another, in a single straight line. But thinking doesn't work that way.

2
00:00:21,333 --> 00:00:30,993
Meet Dendrite - an AI knowledge space where every conversation is a tree, not a feed. Watch the answer stream in, in real time.

3
00:00:31,493 --> 00:00:45,564
Here's the core idea. Select any sentence, and branch. Dendrite spins off a whole new line of inquiry about exactly that, carrying your selection as context. Your main thread stays untouched.

4
00:00:46,064 --> 00:00:56,560
Branches can branch. Chase a tangent as far as you want - every detour becomes its own explorable thread instead of burying what came before.

5
00:00:57,060 --> 00:01:09,180
Open the mind-map and you see the shape of your thinking. The glowing path is where you are now. Tap any node to jump straight back to that moment.

6
00:01:09,680 --> 00:01:19,479
Star the nodes that matter - they light up gold on the map. And search finds any message across every conversation you've had.

7
00:01:19,979 --> 00:01:33,122
Under the hood, one engine speaks to NVIDIA, OpenAI, Anthropic, and Gemini. Bring your own key - it's kept in your device's secure enclave, and every conversation stays local on your phone.

8
00:01:33,622 --> 00:01:44,071
It's local-first, private, and built in Flutter for Android, iOS, and the web - with every pixel carefully polished.

9
00:01:44,571 --> 00:01:52,465
Dendrite. Think in branches, not lines. Try the live demo and explore the code - links below.
